From: alex@psyalex.psy.gu.se ()
Subject: NFS proplems
Reply-To: alex@psyalex.psy.gu.se
Date: Wed, 24 Nov 1993 17:45:35 GMT


Hi !

I've run in to a slight problem. I made a lot of changes
and now I don't know if to blame Linux or not.

I'm currently running 0.99pl13r and the problem occurs
when I try to NFS mount a disk from our HP-server.

The message I get is :
mount clntudp_create: RPC: Program not registered
mount clntudp_create: RPC: Program not registered
mount clntudp_create: RPC: Program not registered

We used to run HP-UX 8.07 on a HP720. Today we uppgraded
to a HP735 with HP-UX 9.01 and I uppgraded my kernel and 
filesystems from the latest SLS to the newer versions of
Linux and e2fs (and the /etc/binaries).

So should I blame Linux or HP ? Of course I suspect HP ;-)

Please answer somebody.

