From: ab401@freenet.carleton.ca (Paul Tomblin)
Subject: Re: Any LINUX installations in real life environments?
Reply-To: ab401@freenet.carleton.ca
Date: Thu, 25 Nov 1993 23:36:51 GMT

poirot@mickey.jsc.nasa.gov (Daniel Poirot) writes:

>I am getting a lot out of Linux at work.  Our inventory follows...
[etc]

My $0.02: Gandalf uses a network of Linux boxes to test network products.  
Each Linux box is connected to two networks: the control network, and the 
network under test.  The boxes have a combination of packet generators, snmp 
slaves, net sniffers and the like - and a master control program running on a 
sparc server controls them all and analyses the results.  They used to use 
SCO Xenix, but found that Linux had better network support, and they could 
hack on it when it didn't work.

